column7:
NOTE: the game evidently does not know how to make its automatic vram allocation work with the giant images used in these next few scenes. i've added a special command here that overrides subtitle placement in vram for the duration of the script to work around the issues this causes.
and on top of that, the game stops querying the cd drive for the current position of XA playback while scrolling over the images, so the subtitle timer has to rely on fallback code that simply assumes a frame has passed every time it updates. this means that lag (caused by preparing and sending the subtitles to vram) accumulates and causes the timer to run too slowly during those periods, so i've had to push the timing slightly ahead for certain lines to compensate.

ユナです
お元気ですか？
ユナはいつも通りとても元気です

この戦いで失ったものもあったけど…

ユナはどんなことがあっても、みんなと一緒に、いつも笑顔でいたいなぁって思ってます
最近は、またお仕事の方は忙しくなって、コンサートの話もあります！
絶対に見に来てほしいな！
別の星にも行きたいな！
そしたら、また色んな人とお友達になれるもんね！
楽しみだな！
いつかまた、あなたに会いたいな
それまでちょっとだけ…
